                <h2 id="travel">Travel <a class="dm-dp-anchorLink" href="#travel">#</a></h2>

                <p>I usually have a list of places I&rsquo;ve traveled in the year, but the list is pretty slim for 2020. From January to March, I traveled to:</p>

                <ol>
                    <li>Banff, Canada</li>
                    <li>Tulum, Mexico</li>
                    <li>Portland, <abbr title="Maine">ME</abbr></li>                    
                </ol>

                <p>Unusually, all of those places were personal trips, not work trips.</p>

                <p>On the bright side, because of the lack of flying this year, I was only <a href="https://twitter.com/danmall/status/1225480375541149696">&ldquo;randomly&rdquo; selected for screening</a> twice this year as opposed to 5 times last year.</p>

                <p>Although we couldn&rsquo;t fly anywhere this year, our family still tried to take some trips together that were all within driving distance.</p>

                <ul>
                    <li>We spent a long weekend in Cape May, <abbr title="New Jersey">NJ</abbr> this summer.</li>
                    <li>We rented a lake house in Northumberland, <abbr title="Pennsylvania">PA</abbr> for a few days this summer and went tubing and kayaking.</li>
                    <li>Em and I took a road trip through New England to see some fall foliage.</li>
                    <li>I took the kids to the Adirondacks to see some fall foliage.</li>
                </ul>

                <p>I&rsquo;m hoping we can fly again in 2021, but if not, I have a feeling we&rsquo;ll get creative about scratching that itch.</p>



                <h2 id="videos-photos">Videos &amp; photos <a class="dm-dp-anchorLink" href="#videos-photos">#</a></h2>

                <p>In last year&rsquo;s review, I lamented doing less video stuff than I had anticipated and hoped that some online course ideas would be enough motivation to change that. I was right! I made a 12-video course about design systems called &ldquo;<a href="https://superfriendlydesign.systems/classes/make-design-systems-people-want-to-use/">Make Design Systems People Want to Use</a>&rdquo; that I wrote, shot, and edited all by myself. I dreaded how long editing takes, but I did underestimate how quickly I could get comfortable in Final Cut Pro after spending some time with YouTube tutorials. Now I don&rsquo;t feel as intimidated about making videos and find myself making fun little 90-second to 2-minute videos of things like preparing a Thanksgiving meal, a silly Christmas play we did a few years ago, or random b-roll from around the house.</p>

                <p>On the photography front, I&rsquo;m still as enthusiastic about taking photos as I was a year ago. I started <a href="http://photos.danmall.me/">my photo site</a> and <a href="https://www.instagram.com/danmallphotos/">Instagram account</a> around this time last year, and I&rsquo;ve posted about 125 photos to them since. Winter without snow on the East Coast of the United States isn&rsquo;t terribly picturesque, so I find myself longing for a photo trip to a super snowy location or for a soon-to-come photogenic season like cherry blossoms in the spring. I&rsquo;m slowly curating a list of photo trips I&rsquo;d like to take soon. In the meantime, I&rsquo;m still taking a few online courses to get better at this hobby, like <a href="https://www.shopmoment.com/lessons/introduction-to-landscape-photography-with-tiffany-nguyen">Introduction to Landscape Photography with Tiffany Nguyen</a>, <a href="https://learn.proedu.com/products/commercial-composites-with-erik-almas">Composite Photography &amp; Retouching for Advertising by Erik Almas</a>, and <a href="https://fabioantenore.ch/produkt/hyperreal-landscapes-bundle/?lang=en">Hyperreal Landscapes</a>.</p>

                <p>I expect to do a lot more photo and video stuff in 2021.</p>

